text:

author: @acutelilmint8035
text:
I choose b - money. 
Reason - if I have 2.2 billion friends, is it because they wanted to be my friends ? Or is it this magic wish that forced them to be my friend? And do these friends love and like each other? Will these friends end up competing to be my best friend and start wars?  If this isn’t free will.. the. Having that many friends is no different than having yes men all around you like in hollywood who are only your friend cause of clout..

It gotta be free will.. same with, if you wish for someone to love you, is that real love? #teamfreewill.  So I agree with ravenclaw guy.. a few very good friends . Also 2.2 billion dollars you can help a bunch of people who aren’t your friends…and if they want, they can become your friend…

But as a lonely infp, 2.2 billion friends - I wouldn’t have panic attacks going out cause everyone is my friend haha

author: @acutelilmint8035
text:
There’s another thing called vultology which I think is more acccurate.. it focuses on how we look and move.. and because peopel use different parts of their brain, it eventually shapes ur face based off the muscles you use..  also because of diff thinking process, you see it through body and hand movement too. I think it’s pretty cool.  P and J ,T, F you can really tell there is a difference there, and with eyes the shapes, which muscles are use sometimes explain why certain people with certain personalities seem to give off same vibe or have similar eyes.

Like S people tend to have sharper eyes vs N.. if you pay attention, you can even start to see where people are thinking ( internally , externally).

Take it with a grain of salt, but it’s pretty fun to try spotting patterns and stuff in behaviour and looks vs just what people say(cause I think anyone can really think of the same conclusions but it’s where they are thinking that shapes them..I dunno haha

author: @miahgrass2511
text: As an INFJ, I was so surprised to see Jungwoo picked 2.2 billion friends over money. I was 100% on Doyoung and Kun's side haha. No it's not about the money at all, it's about not being able to maintain that huge number of relationships, that's not something a typical introvert can handle. As an introvert, my energy usually gets drained off when there are too many people around, not to mention just thinking about how to balance all my relationships already makes me stressed out. I also agree with Doyoung about treating our friends wholeheartedly, it's like an unspoken responsibility toward them. Having 2.2 billion friends is not a privilege, it's a nightmare.

author: @twisted_introvert
text:
Why does the poop debate, in particular, remind me of SVT's Debate Night series? 😆
Their debates were so funny!  I'm glad they enjoyed getting together and hearing and expressing various opinions.
(Alright Mr. Johnny "that's because you're narrow minded" Suh, as an introvert who's been in the situation of having a friend bring a "+1 (or 3)", let me open your own mind a bit.  It's got nothing to do w/ how broad my perspective is, it's got to do with my energy levels and how I function fundamentally.  I was mentally prepared to interact with one person and even with that prep & my love for my friend, it would be a drain on my energy.  Adding another into the mix throws me off and drains me even more.  "The more the merrier," especially unexpectedly, is rarely an introvert's mindset and rather than gaining energy from interacting with others as extroverts do, it depletes my energy.  I'm with Jisung in that I'd be disappointed [and probably a little angry] w/ my friend.)

author: @idkwtd5565
text:
as a psychology student, they really represents the mbti really well. i would like to point out the n vs s debate.  N stands for intuition  while S stands for sensing and its the way we perceive things. N has more imagination  and perceive the something beyond its physical appearance while S is more objective and looks more at the reality. as the question  was revealed, we can see how the Ns are more active in giving their opinion. its because the zombie situation is something you have to imagine, especially johnny who come up with all sorts of scenes. while the Ss we see somewhat cant really grasp the idea of zombies coming to their place and they gave like really general ideas of how theyll face the situation. while Ns actually talks like the zombies are coming and they could tell details of how theyre gonna face it.

thats all. however, as a reminder, mbti is one of the personality test that have a low validity and reliability. most psychologist dont really use it to assess someones personality. but it is the most famous one due to its easiness to interpret and its suitable for people who dont have a psychology background

Also, maybe I have been scorned by too many people that I considered my friend that I am more cautious as well.

text:
just a little bit of analysis on the Chapter One balance game

Q1 - 2.2 Bio of friends or 2.2 Bio money

- The ones who choose A (Jungwoo, Jisung, Johnny) are all the N (Intuition) type, and the ones who choose B (Sungchan, Doyoung, Kun) are all S (Sensing) type

Q2 - Rumor of you eating poop or You actually did eat poop but nobody knows
- The ones who choose A (Johnny, Kun) are all Extrovert, and the ones who choose B (Jungwoo, Doyoung, Jisung, and aside for Sungchan) are mostly Introvert

I  took too much interest in this kind of thing, I know 🤣

author: @4everlastingstarlight
text:
I noticed this, none of nct members have a extremely dominant percentage in their mbti traits. Like feelers are also use  thinking a lot or judgers have no problems at using perceiving in a moment of stress. I think this is one of the key elements how they can keep their friendship (talking about ones who knew each other for years) and teamwork. 

Ps: For ones who don't know percentages, no one depends on only one trait in their daily life. Feelers sometimes use thinking depending on the situation they're in, or introverts can get energised from a right crowd too. The results show which one is more dominant, for example if you are %10 introverted and %90 extroverted your mbti type will start with E however the result would be same if you're %48 introverted and %52 extroverted. This also makes an explanation for the fact people with the same type can be very different than each other

author: @taeyongforcleansingyourski7278
text:
Aku INFP kayak Jisung, tapi ada beberapa aku yang berseberangan.
Misalnya pilih 2,2 M uang atau 2,2 M teman. Aku pilih 2,2 M uang. Karena temen deket bagiku udah cukup, paling gak 3 orang, 2,2 M kebanyakan. Karena aku gak suka ketemu dengan orang yang terlalu banyak, habis energi. Mending punya banyak uang aja sih.

Terus kalo temenku bawa temen tanpa pemberitahuan ini lebih kondisional aja kayaknya. Kalo cuma untuk ketemuan sekadar nongkrong aja gak apa-apa. Tapi kalo curhat, kayaknya aku bakalan kecewa juga.

Terus kalo masalah makan, aku juga kondisional, kalo udah terlalu laper, aku bakal makan apa aja yang terdekat dari tempat yang dituju kalo tempat itu tutup. Tapi kalo beneran lagi pengen banget, aku bakalan cari makanan sejenis meski jauh.

author: @Bunny-ct9li
text: I always get upset or mad(not totally) when ppl does not like what I cooked or they will say it’s too salty or bland. But I am not upset because it taste like that, even me myself knows if I did cook good or not. I get upset because cooking takes time and effort😂I get to wash and chop everything for some time, my sweat is all over my face and in the end all I got were complaints?🤣 But I am also that person who’d rather be honest to someone if they cook and it taste no good, that is because how would they learn if you keep on telling em lies?what will be their progress if you will always say it is okay or it is good when it is not🤣 yes I am that type of person, I do not like ppl complaining about mine but I also prefer to be honest to others about their food😂🙈 maybe because of my pride?and maybe it is because of how the person reacts to it, if u say it is salty in a nice,non-offensive way why would I be upset right? but if my sister complains about my food, damn girl u better be chef Ramsay to have the audacity🤣👊

author: @beyandat
text:
"All you are thinking is just giving of something to a friend. But you also get something in return. That's how friends are."

Whoa. What Johnny said really amazes me. I love this kind of mentality. Friendship is not a one-way relationship. It's always a two-way interaction. You can't just give all that you have for a friend to the point that you lose yourself in the process. At the same time, you can't just always receive love and care from your friends all the time. You have to reciprocate, not out of duty, but out of appreciation towards them. Such beautiful insight from our Daddy Suh. 💚


DISCLAIMER: This is not, in any way, throwing shade or hate towards what Doyoung said. This comment is merely an appreciation towards Johnny's words of wisdom. Also, I hope Doyoung sees that he is not *obliged* to always give something to a friend, to single-handedly carry the friendship. He is so selfless that he even thought he should give extra effort. Honey, your members are with you. They will take care of you, love you, and appreciate you. It's always okay to accept love and care. You are not alone.

NCT are friendship goals.

author: @raisha99
text:
My answers as an ISFP

Chapter ONE

Q1 (9:28)
Money ofc it's obvious. And realistically speaking, I don't think it's possible to interact with 2.2B people as your friends even being a celebrity.
Q2 (13:54)
A because I'll never in lay life eat shit. And even if I did and people don't know it'd still be embarrassing and I couldn't live with that. If there's rumor I'd just tell people I care about the truth and I trust they'd believe.

Chapter TWO

E vs I (16:32)
Like jisung said, I'd not be happy about it if they didn't say anything beforehand. But even if they did I wouldn't enjoy it that well either bcs I'm really awkward with new people. Tho I wouldn't say the feeling is disappointment, more like discomfort and awkwardness.

N vs S (18:53)
I'd evacuate ig? Idk I don't really like to think about the possibility of me personally experiencing the end of the world. This is the reason I don't really read or watch stuff with apocalyptic theme.

F vs T (22:49)
It really depends actually... If it's really bad I can't help my expression for sure and just be honest. But if it's not that bad I'd say "it's ok ig" or "hmm not bad". If there are other people besides me I'd hear their opinions first and give mine accordingly haha.

P vs J (24:37)
I'd go to nearby place bcs I don't like being on the road for too long. When traveling, the trip I have to make to go places is the most annoying part that makes me not like travelling. I never traveled alone before so the planning was always done by others, but if I'm gonna travel alone, I'd probably just make rough plan. I don't know if my answers match my mbti😂

author: @CatsAndOrchestra
text:
Doyoung saying 10:18 "Then, that friend may say I GAVE you 40,00 won LAST TIME" screams ISFJ/Si-dom!!!
The reason why Doyoung hold grudges is because of his dominant function, "Si" (introverted sensing). ISFJ and ISTJ are very good at reflecting past experiences, valuing tradition and routines, and stabilizing their life. ISFJs and ISTJs are can also describe past experiences in detail and give realistic and specific examples. 

However, this mindset can be sometimes frustrating for Ne and Ni-doms (ENFP, ENTP, INFJ, INTJ) since they are very future-oriented and prefers the bigger picture of things. You often see Johnny and Haechan arguing with Doyoung because they sometimes find the Si-dom mindset too past-oriented and inflexible. Their long friendship makes the combination work tho! 😊
